The construction of this specific machine emphasizes an open-source, custom-fabricated approach typical of 
student engineering projects and DIY makerspace builds. The frame combines standard rigid components,
such as black metal extrusions and smooth linear guide rods, with custom orange and pink structural brackets. 
These colorful brackets are themselves 3D-printed components. Surrounding the printer in 3D CANTILELEVER are 
various fabrication tools, including a hardware organizer filled with screws, a socket set, 
and detached extruder feed mechanisms, emphasizing that this machine is in an active phase of assembly, calibration,
or maintenance.
